54
00:04:29,671 --> 00:04:29,831
[SPEAKER_07]: So.

55
00:04:32,237 --> 00:04:43,280
[SPEAKER_07]: The MSBA requires that we construct a school building committee that shepherds this project from now until completion.

56
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:53,643
[SPEAKER_07]: There are some requirements laid out in the regulations and is sort of the basis of how MSBA will

57
00:04:54,343 --> 00:04:56,465
[SPEAKER_07]: evaluate our building committee and ultimately approve it.

58
00:04:56,485 --> 00:05:07,613
[SPEAKER_07]: So that is a step that we will go through once the committee is formed, is that it will go to the MSBA's legal team and they will weigh in and say, yes, we believe this committee is appropriate for the scope and scale of the work.

59
00:05:09,174 --> 00:05:15,919
[SPEAKER_07]: So what you see here is a sort of a listing by law, by reg, of what those requirements are.

60
00:05:15,939 --> 00:05:15,979
[SPEAKER_07]: So

61
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:34,992
[SPEAKER_07]: In our case, many of these roles are sort of dual roles, but this is written broadly because it has to sort of accommodate for cities and towns and strong mayor communities and distributed communities that don't have a strong mayor system and they have a town manager.

62
00:05:35,012 --> 00:05:37,434
[SPEAKER_07]: So there's lots of sort of iterations of all of this.

63
00:05:38,514 --> 00:05:43,478
[SPEAKER_07]: For us, the requirements sort of roughly that apply to us

64
00:05:44,178 --> 00:05:49,939
[SPEAKER_07]: our A, which is the local chief executive officer that is the mayor.

65
00:05:49,959 --> 00:05:55,421
[SPEAKER_07]: B does not apply to us because we don't have a town administrator or town manager.

66
00:05:56,381 --> 00:06:01,842
[SPEAKER_07]: At least one member of the school committee that applies to us, the superintendent of schools applies to us.

67
00:06:02,823 --> 00:06:06,883
[SPEAKER_07]: The local official responsible for building maintenance applies for Medford.

68
00:06:08,124 --> 00:06:12,485
[SPEAKER_07]: A representative of the office or body authorized by law to construct

69
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:31,320
[SPEAKER_07]: School buildings, I actually had some conversation with the MSBA, that means the mayor here in Medford, the school principal from the school in question, as well as a member who's knowledgeable about the educational mission and function of the facility.

70
00:06:32,501 --> 00:06:37,245
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll talk about who satisfies those roles when we get into the weeds here in Medford.

71
00:06:38,225 --> 00:06:41,826
[SPEAKER_07]: A local budget official or member of the local finance committee.

72
00:06:41,866 --> 00:06:46,168
[SPEAKER_07]: So in our case, that is Bob Dickinson, who's the CFO for the city.

73
00:06:47,028 --> 00:06:53,250
[SPEAKER_07]: And then the last piece is members of the community with architecture, engineering, and or construction experience.

74
00:06:54,111 --> 00:06:57,752
[SPEAKER_07]: So that's what the MSBA requires by law just to set the stage.

75
00:07:00,124 --> 00:07:11,266
[SPEAKER_07]: The next piece of the resolution talks a little bit about the goals that we're trying to keep in mind as we construct this committee.

76
00:07:12,126 --> 00:07:17,267
[SPEAKER_07]: Once we turn our attention to some editing, we may decide that there's other things here.

77
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:24,729
[SPEAKER_07]: But what I tried to do was lay something out for everybody to react to and say, yes, I like it or let's change this or that.

78
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:47,338
[SPEAKER_07]: The big one is to plan comprehensively for all programming that currently resides at Medford High, which includes vocational, non-vocational 9-12 education, 9-12 athletics, Medford Family Network, Medford Community Schools programming, early childhood education, including but not limited to the MEET program in Kids' Corner.

79
00:07:47,918 --> 00:07:52,560
[SPEAKER_07]: We think about this as a high school, but in fact, there's quite a lot that goes on in that building that is

80
00:07:54,521 --> 00:08:01,124
[SPEAKER_07]: bigger than simply what happens in the 9 to 12 space.

81
00:08:02,024 --> 00:08:10,988
[SPEAKER_07]: Number two is to consider whether placement of the Curtis Tufts Alternative High School on the campus will provide increased educational opportunities to enrolled students.

82
00:08:11,968 --> 00:08:17,811
[SPEAKER_07]: Number three is to ensure a robust public input and stakeholder feedback at appropriate milestones throughout the project.

83
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:26,414
[SPEAKER_07]: Number 4 is to listen to educator and administrator input regarding the future of educational best practices and plans for the students of Medford.

84
00:08:27,334 --> 00:08:37,299
[SPEAKER_07]: Number 5, create plans for a building that advances Medford's climate goals and achieves LEED version 5 certification to meet the Paris Climate Accords 2030 and 2050 targets.

85
00:08:37,839 --> 00:08:39,240
[SPEAKER_07]: So we are building a school for

86
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:42,381
[SPEAKER_07]: 50 years, maybe more, hopefully more.

87
00:08:44,101 --> 00:09:00,145
[SPEAKER_07]: And we have to be sort of thinking forward about what, what impacts on the environment that our building will have, and on our goals, and then moves efficiently and effectively through the building process in a manner that ensures students are able to learn in the new building as quickly as is feasible.

88
00:09:00,205 --> 00:09:04,686
[SPEAKER_07]: So I think that's obviously very top of mind for everybody here.

89
00:09:06,186 --> 00:09:09,607
[SPEAKER_07]: But that so that's sort of what I framed up as the goals.

90
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:13,937
[SPEAKER_07]: Member Rousseau, I see that we may have a student representative with us.

91
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:15,882
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes, I've already put her on.

92
00:09:15,942 --> 00:09:17,025
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, welcome Noah.

93
00:09:20,099 --> 00:09:28,502
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, the next piece of the resolution lays out some of the authority and responsibility of the chair of the committee, and that's me.

94
00:09:29,703 --> 00:09:37,887
[SPEAKER_07]: But I wanted to outline my thinking about the kinds of things the school committee needs to be able to reasonably expect from the chair.

95
00:09:37,907 --> 00:09:43,950
[SPEAKER_07]: The chair would recommend extensions of member terms subject to approval by the Medford School Committee.

96
00:09:45,831 --> 00:10:09,211
[SPEAKER_07]: recommend replacement of non-participatory members subject to approval by this committee, work with the appointed committee to maintain various subcommittees including, but not limited to communication and community engagement, sustainability, mechanical, electrical and plumbing, finance, and then other committees that will ebb and flow over the life of the project depending on what's going on.

97
00:10:11,309 --> 00:10:17,873
[SPEAKER_07]: Number four, work with the appointed committee to convene external advisory committees and consultancy on an as-needed basis.

98
00:10:18,354 --> 00:10:30,222
[SPEAKER_07]: This committee will be out doing competitive bid processes for folks to do the feasibility study, for people to do schematic design, people to do building.

99
00:10:30,923 --> 00:10:35,186
[SPEAKER_07]: This group will do that and so the chair will

100
00:10:35,826 --> 00:10:42,832
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll work with the committee to convene those experts sort of in accordance with the rules and the regs of MSBA.

101
00:10:44,013 --> 00:10:55,342
[SPEAKER_07]: Provide monthly updates to the school committee so that there is an ongoing flow of information back to the school committee, and then act in accordance with MSBA's rules and regs on behalf of the school committee.

102
00:10:56,263 --> 00:11:04,010
[SPEAKER_07]: And then finally, just a note that our first update of the building committee's governing structure scope

103
00:11:05,188 --> 00:11:10,699
[SPEAKER_07]: resources, community engagement plans, website, document management plans, and training sometime in May.

104
00:11:10,779 --> 00:11:14,166
[SPEAKER_07]: So thinking that second meeting in the month of May.

105
00:11:18,408 --> 00:11:24,669
[SPEAKER_07]: Overall, what is outlined in the resolution is a proposal that the committee would be 15 voting members.

106
00:11:25,849 --> 00:11:32,411
[SPEAKER_07]: I had some conversation with the MSBA to understand what the rules and requirements are around voting versus non-voting members.

107
00:11:32,491 --> 00:11:45,213
[SPEAKER_07]: And the answer is there are really no hard and fast rules about who must be a voting member and who can be a non-voting member, that that changes pretty dramatically community to community.

108
00:11:47,551 --> 00:11:58,056
[SPEAKER_07]: But it's important to note that all these meetings are subject to the open meeting law, which does mean that voting members have to produce a quorum in order to be able to meet and they're subject to all the same rules that we are.

109
00:11:58,777 --> 00:12:01,838
[SPEAKER_07]: So, from an appointees perspective, what this.

110
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:08,383
[SPEAKER_07]: What this resolution would do is formally appoint the people that you see on this slide.

111
00:12:08,463 --> 00:12:17,970
[SPEAKER_07]: So that would be myself, the mayor, Dr. Edward Vincent, Mrs. Galussi, Dr. Cushing, and Ms.

112
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:19,871
[SPEAKER_07]: Cabral, who's the principal at Medford High.

113
00:12:19,971 --> 00:12:23,914
[SPEAKER_07]: So we would be formally appointing those six people as voting members.

114
00:12:24,634 --> 00:12:31,299
[SPEAKER_07]: We would also be identifying a number of non-voting members who will participate in the committee

115
00:12:33,642 --> 00:12:47,998
[SPEAKER_07]: and be integral to the discussion and all of the work that goes on just as much as any voting member, but will not vote when it comes time to vote or be needed in the case of a quorum.

116
00:12:48,058 --> 00:12:51,321
[SPEAKER_07]: So Bob Dickinson, who is our local budget official, is one of those folks.

117
00:12:52,623 --> 00:12:59,008
[SPEAKER_07]: Somebody from the city who is a certified public purchasing official, that is a requirement of MSBA.

118
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:10,298
[SPEAKER_07]: And there is somebody in the procurement office who holds this certification who will be appointed to the committee, and I'm not sure about their name, which is why they are to be determined.

119
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:22,971
[SPEAKER_07]: Chad Fallon, who is the Director of the Medford Vocational School, Joan Bowen, our Director of People's Services, John McLaughlin, who's our Director of Buildings and Grounds, and Tom Dalton, who is our Director of Communications.

120
00:13:23,011 --> 00:13:26,835
[SPEAKER_07]: So all would be appointed to the committee in a non-voting capacity.

121
00:13:29,483 --> 00:13:37,810
[SPEAKER_07]: And then to fill out, so that's, that is, sorry, six members, six voting members.

122
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:50,221
[SPEAKER_07]: So we would be seeking applications to appoint nine additional members, one more school committee member, one city counselor, and then seven open positions to fill out.

123
00:13:51,282 --> 00:13:56,386
[SPEAKER_07]: who all would comprise voting members of the committee who are residents of Medford.

124
00:13:56,446 --> 00:14:05,934
[SPEAKER_07]: So Medford public school teachers and staff who are residents of Medford are welcome to apply to fill any number of those seven spots.

125
00:14:07,015 --> 00:14:14,422
[SPEAKER_07]: And then keeping in mind that we also need to be able to demonstrate that we have members of the community with architecture, engineering and or construction experience.

126
00:14:16,263 --> 00:14:17,906
[SPEAKER_07]: who are on the committee as a requirement.

127
00:14:17,966 --> 00:14:28,525
[SPEAKER_07]: So those seven open positions for residents could contain any mix of people with various skills.

128
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:32,425
[SPEAKER_07]: We're almost there.

129
00:14:32,445 --> 00:14:47,550
[SPEAKER_07]: The last sort of final piece of the resolution talks about the questions that we'll ask on the application that we'll put out shortly if we are able to get through any edits to this process tonight.

130
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:53,533
[SPEAKER_07]: and obviously some of the basics, name, address, et cetera.

131
00:14:53,953 --> 00:15:02,478
[SPEAKER_07]: We can go through this in detail, but really trying to understand why do you want to be on the building committee as a very important question.

132
00:15:03,478 --> 00:15:14,204
[SPEAKER_07]: Really giving people an opportunity to tell us what excites them about this opportunity, and also give people an opportunity to

133
00:15:16,471 --> 00:15:24,600
[SPEAKER_07]: let them tell us in their own words sort of how they are thinking about potentially being members of the committee.

134
00:15:26,534 --> 00:15:42,146
[SPEAKER_07]: We do want to know if you are related to any member of the Medford School Committee, and then some sort of basic things that will help us facilitate meetings, whether an interpreter will be required and confirmation that people can participate actively in Zoom.

135
00:15:42,266 --> 00:15:47,490
[SPEAKER_07]: So I think we will have a mix of meetings, but we want to make sure that people are comfortable with that format.

136
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:52,391
[SPEAKER_07]: and then trying to understand a little bit about the applicant.

137
00:15:52,651 --> 00:15:54,151
[SPEAKER_07]: Are you a teacher or staff member?

138
00:15:54,171 --> 00:15:57,172
[SPEAKER_07]: Do you have experience in school building projects?

139
00:15:57,932 --> 00:16:02,373
[SPEAKER_07]: Do you have communications and management experience of large-scale programs like this?

140
00:16:04,054 --> 00:16:07,635
[SPEAKER_07]: What other expertise do you have that you think is really relevant to tell us about?

141
00:16:08,975 --> 00:16:09,955
[SPEAKER_07]: Are you a student?

142
00:16:10,835 --> 00:16:11,716
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll want to know that.

143
00:16:12,616 --> 00:16:15,096
[SPEAKER_07]: Are you the caregiver of a Medford public school student?

144
00:16:15,676 --> 00:16:17,637
[SPEAKER_07]: If so, tell us about your student.

145
00:16:20,719 --> 00:16:32,768
[SPEAKER_07]: And then confirmation that you can commit to twice monthly meetings that will be held on Monday evenings in person and potentially on Zoom over time.

146
00:16:35,422 --> 00:16:51,366
[SPEAKER_07]: that you are prepared to commit through the entire eligibility phase of the project, which is through June 26, 2025, and that you are willing and able to commit to this appointment through the entire project, which may last up to seven years.

147
00:16:52,006 --> 00:17:01,188
[SPEAKER_07]: So this first term, sort of the way it's proposed is that it would be through the eligibility phase, but the desire and expectation is that

148
00:17:02,148 --> 00:17:05,890
[SPEAKER_07]: we're not turning over this committee and in sort of wholesale fashion.

149
00:17:05,990 --> 00:17:09,771
[SPEAKER_07]: So we want to make sure people understand that this is quite a long commitment.

150
00:17:11,552 --> 00:17:14,453
[SPEAKER_07]: It will be intense in various periods of time.

151
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:22,837
[SPEAKER_07]: And it's, it's, you know, somewhere between five and seven years of, of effort to see this project to fruition.

152
00:17:24,849 --> 00:17:32,838
[SPEAKER_07]: We actively support and participate in a public campaign to secure funding from Everett's taxpayers to pay for aspects of the project not directly supported by MSBA.

153
00:17:33,439 --> 00:17:41,608
[SPEAKER_07]: So I think that's really important to understand how people are thinking about the eventuality here, which is that we will have to pay for

154
00:17:42,669 --> 00:17:45,131
[SPEAKER_07]: a project in some capacity.

155
00:17:45,192 --> 00:17:50,056
[SPEAKER_07]: So MSBA, we hope will pay for lots of it, but there will be a taxpayer impact here.

156
00:17:50,816 --> 00:17:55,380
[SPEAKER_07]: And we want to hear from people about their perspective on that in the application process.

157
00:17:56,974 --> 00:18:21,249
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll ask some demographics questions just for us to be able to understand who's applying because I think this group has done a thoughtful job in past committee formations to make sure that there is representation from a wide variety of stakeholders on the committee and we need some of this information to help us understand

158
00:18:22,150 --> 00:18:30,336
[SPEAKER_07]: who's applying and who hasn't applied so that we can put the best, most effective committee together that we possibly can.

159
00:18:30,356 --> 00:18:32,478
[SPEAKER_07]: And then are you a registered voter?

160
00:18:32,498 --> 00:18:34,599
[SPEAKER_07]: And if you are, what's your ward and precinct?

161
00:18:34,639 --> 00:18:36,721
[SPEAKER_07]: So again, really thinking about representation.

162
00:18:38,468 --> 00:18:54,629
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, so that was in a very quick nutshell what we are here to talk about tonight, and I am going to pull up a copy of the resolution.

163
00:18:56,637 --> 00:19:11,226
[SPEAKER_07]: And my proposal is that we would just spend some time going through it section by section and talk about any questions that you all have section by section as we go or any edits.

164
00:19:11,286 --> 00:19:18,370
[SPEAKER_07]: So I'm gonna put this into suggestion mode so that you all can see any changes that are being proposed.

165
00:19:18,410 --> 00:19:22,192
[SPEAKER_07]: So it makes it a little bit easier for people to sort of stick with us and track.

166
00:19:23,953 --> 00:19:25,454
[SPEAKER_07]: Any questions so far, member Rousseau?

