330
00:33:30,331 --> 00:33:42,317
[SPEAKER_07]: The next section, now therefore be it resolved that the Medford School Committee, let's do the first five of these, and then we'll carry on.

331
00:33:42,417 --> 00:33:45,838
[SPEAKER_07]: Number one, establishes the Medford Comprehensive High School Building Committee.

332
00:33:46,359 --> 00:33:48,860
[SPEAKER_07]: Said committee may be referred to as the School Building Committee.

333
00:33:49,380 --> 00:34:15,625
[SPEAKER_07]: acknowledges that the significant investment members of the committee are making in the future of the city of Medford and Medford Public Schools, and regrets that the positions cannot be compensated in compliance with MSBA rules and regulations, grants the authority of the school building committee chair to recommend extensions of member terms subject to approval by the Medford School Committee, recommend replacement of non-participatory members subject to approval by the Medford School Committee,

334
00:34:16,825 --> 00:34:32,375
[SPEAKER_07]: work with the appointed committee to maintain various subcommittees including, but not limited to, communication and community engagement, sustainability, mechanical, electrical, and plumbing, finance, and other committees as established by the chair.

335
00:34:33,595 --> 00:34:39,738
[SPEAKER_07]: D, work with the appointed committee to convene external advisory committees and consultancy on an as-needed basis.

336
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:43,120
[SPEAKER_07]: E, provide monthly updates to the Medford School Committee.

337
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:50,063
[SPEAKER_07]: And F, act in accordance with MSBA established rules, regulations, and requirements on behalf of the school building committee.

338
00:34:51,169 --> 00:35:04,548
[SPEAKER_07]: Um, number 4 requires a report to be presented to the member school committee regarding the school building committees governing structure scope resources, community engagement plans, website and document management plans and training no later than May 20th, 2024.

339
00:35:06,831 --> 00:35:30,730
[SPEAKER_07]: And number 5, establishes the initial term of members beginning April 15, 2024, which is the start of Medford's eligibility phase is May 1st, and ending January 25th, 26th, sorry, 2025, which is 270 days from the start of our eligibility phase, or the successful completion of the eligibility phase, whichever is sooner.

340
00:35:31,251 --> 00:35:32,632
[SPEAKER_07]: The school committee desires

341
00:35:33,252 --> 00:35:40,778
[SPEAKER_07]: Stability in the committee and will extend member terms throughout each phase of the process at the recommendation of the chair.

342
00:35:41,759 --> 00:35:46,502
[SPEAKER_07]: So that is numbers 1 through 5 questions.

343
00:35:47,943 --> 00:35:48,804
