700
01:11:55,186 --> 01:12:00,908
[SPEAKER_07]: All meetings are public meetings and will be conducted in accordance with the open meeting law using Robert's Rules of Order.

701
01:12:02,769 --> 01:12:04,169
[SPEAKER_07]: Questions, comments, thoughts?

702
01:12:07,988 --> 01:12:18,673
[SPEAKER_08]: I worry a little bit about getting all community members up to speed on Robert's Rules of Order, but if that's how open meeting has to be, that's how it has to be.

703
01:12:22,955 --> 01:12:28,201
[SPEAKER_07]: The mayor has been able to secure training for other commissions.

704
01:12:28,501 --> 01:12:34,427
[SPEAKER_07]: I believe the Charter Study Committee went through a similar process.

705
01:12:34,787 --> 01:12:38,992
[SPEAKER_07]: So we'll bring in somebody to help accelerate that process, I believe.

706
01:12:39,873 --> 01:12:40,033
[SPEAKER_07]: Great.

707
01:12:42,173 --> 01:12:48,136
[SPEAKER_07]: The other request that the mayor had was to potentially move the April 8th date.

708
01:12:49,236 --> 01:12:51,077
[SPEAKER_07]: April 8th is a committee meeting.

709
01:12:52,577 --> 01:12:56,079
[SPEAKER_07]: The next committee meeting is not until the 29th.

710
01:13:00,115 --> 01:13:07,477
[SPEAKER_07]: And so we would if we did move that we would also have to move our we would have to serve slide.

711
01:13:09,338 --> 01:13:14,159
[SPEAKER_07]: Our May 1st date and our report to the school committee on May 20th.

712
01:13:15,339 --> 01:13:24,062
[SPEAKER_07]: So that was the other question she asked us to consider in this meeting, so I will open that to the floor member so.

713
01:13:24,142 --> 01:13:28,443
[SPEAKER_01]: I certainly appreciate that the mayor wants that that this is.

714
01:13:29,559 --> 01:13:40,649
[SPEAKER_01]: My recommendation I my concern is just that our our eligibility opens on May 1st and that is not something that we can slide or change that's the state has determined that and it happens whether we're ready or not.

715
01:13:42,291 --> 01:13:50,098
[SPEAKER_01]: And if we do move it later than April 8th, then we will certainly not be having our 1st building committee meeting on the 1st and.

716
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:57,043
[SPEAKER_01]: People will still not have had a chance to be trained on open meeting law and Robert's rules.

717
01:13:57,604 --> 01:14:01,467
[SPEAKER_01]: And I feel like we're going to be moving into the middle of May before the 1st meeting happens.

718
01:14:02,327 --> 01:14:08,712
[SPEAKER_01]: And, you know, that whole what's that process to have in meetings of the forming and norming that has to happen.

719
01:14:09,012 --> 01:14:12,355
[SPEAKER_01]: So we're going to be in June before this committee is doing any real work.

720
01:14:13,516 --> 01:14:14,677
[SPEAKER_01]: I just very much.

721
01:14:16,313 --> 01:14:21,976
[SPEAKER_01]: I understand that April 8th feels like it's around the corner because my Lord, it really is.

722
01:14:23,256 --> 01:14:32,060
[SPEAKER_01]: But because of April vacation, I would not be in favor of that move because it really just kind of hoses us on the May 1st start date.

723
01:14:33,281 --> 01:14:38,063
[SPEAKER_01]: And as I think everybody here knows, we do not want to be dilly-dallying.

724
01:14:39,263 --> 01:14:40,864
[SPEAKER_01]: That's the technical term.

725
01:14:43,806 --> 01:14:44,546
[SPEAKER_06]: I completely agree.

726
01:14:45,652 --> 01:14:48,233
[SPEAKER_06]: I agree with that.

727
01:14:48,273 --> 01:14:53,675
[SPEAKER_07]: We cannot wait.

728
01:14:54,495 --> 01:14:58,837
[SPEAKER_07]: Superintendent, maybe what we can do is set a meeting.

729
01:14:58,877 --> 01:15:11,222
[SPEAKER_07]: I know the mayor's calendar is challenging so maybe we can set a meeting now in anticipation of when we can begin that work to put the recommendation together for the committee so that we are ready for you.

730
01:15:12,758 --> 01:15:17,383
[SPEAKER_04]: I was going to actually offer a friendly amendment because of the April vacation week.

731
01:15:18,944 --> 01:15:31,536
[SPEAKER_04]: Since April 8th is a scheduled regular meeting, is it possible that the committee would be open to just doing an additional special meeting on a different date other than the 8th?

732
01:15:38,834 --> 01:15:39,674
[SPEAKER_07]: We could do that.

733
01:15:39,954 --> 01:15:46,217
[SPEAKER_07]: I wondered, though, if we, I think we will also have budget meetings scheduled during that time.

734
01:15:46,237 --> 01:15:47,777
[SPEAKER_07]: Am I?

735
01:15:47,797 --> 01:15:49,478
[SPEAKER_04]: That is true.

736
01:15:49,838 --> 01:15:50,138
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

737
01:15:50,858 --> 01:15:53,139
[SPEAKER_07]: So how about this?

738
01:15:53,379 --> 01:16:02,983
[SPEAKER_07]: Maybe we leave it as it stands, and if we have to make some movement of the timeline, we can come back to the committee and let them know.

739
01:16:04,653 --> 01:16:05,034
[SPEAKER_07]: Uh, member.

740
01:16:05,074 --> 01:16:17,648
[SPEAKER_01]: So, yes, I, you started to say something and that reminded me also that, like, um, open meeting law does allow scheduling related changes to happen without formal meetings or any postings of any sort.

741
01:16:17,768 --> 01:16:20,451
[SPEAKER_01]: So this is actually part of the resolution for which we can just.

742
01:16:21,732 --> 01:16:24,094
[SPEAKER_01]: have a group email, and that is acceptable.

743
01:16:25,255 --> 01:16:29,919
[SPEAKER_01]: So I like the dates being written down so that we have a plan.

744
01:16:30,699 --> 01:16:37,005
[SPEAKER_01]: But if they need to move, for whatever reason, we can move them without scheduling a meeting to do all this work again.

745
01:16:41,909 --> 01:16:44,191
[SPEAKER_07]: Any other questions or comments?

746
01:16:47,107 --> 01:16:50,669
[SPEAKER_08]: I have a question for Dr. Edward Vincent.

747
01:16:50,789 --> 01:16:57,615
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm wondering what the status of the project website is as per the last resolution to set that up.

748
01:17:00,357 --> 01:17:04,900
[SPEAKER_04]: I will definitely be able to, I don't have a formal answer right now.

749
01:17:05,080 --> 01:17:11,985
[SPEAKER_04]: I will speak with Thomas and see if I'm able to get more information on that.

750
01:17:14,675 --> 01:17:21,024
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, so we're just working on pinning down a domain, a URL.

751
01:17:21,946 --> 01:17:25,170
[SPEAKER_02]: The URL from the resolution was already taken, unfortunately.

752
01:17:25,191 --> 01:17:27,254
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, I just looked.

753
01:17:27,674 --> 01:17:28,836
[SPEAKER_02]: It wasn't when we wrote it.

754
01:17:29,717 --> 01:17:37,382
[SPEAKER_02]: So Dr. Cushing's been working on getting a different suitable URL.

755
01:17:37,542 --> 01:17:39,924
[SPEAKER_02]: I think we'll probably have that done very soon.

756
01:17:40,044 --> 01:17:50,912
[SPEAKER_02]: And then it's just a matter of Lisa Miller, our website architect, and I will put together a kind of preliminary page and we'll get it published.

757
01:17:51,712 --> 01:17:58,477
[SPEAKER_02]: We're just basically waiting to pin down a URL and then obviously to do the necessary work to pull one together.

758
01:18:00,467 --> 01:18:00,827
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

759
01:18:01,787 --> 01:18:02,927
[SPEAKER_07]: Member Rousseau, did you have your hand in the air?

760
01:18:03,408 --> 01:18:03,808
[SPEAKER_01]: I did.

761
01:18:03,828 --> 01:18:09,069
[SPEAKER_01]: I feel like when you said that, I was going to start singing a song about that.

762
01:18:09,569 --> 01:18:12,949
[SPEAKER_01]: I'd like to make a motion to approve the resolution as amended.

763
01:18:14,249 --> 01:18:17,230
[SPEAKER_07]: Motion to approve the resolution as amended by Member Rousseau.

764
01:18:17,250 --> 01:18:23,831
[SPEAKER_07]: Is there a second?

765
01:18:24,011 --> 01:18:24,371
[SPEAKER_07]: Second.

766
01:18:25,451 --> 01:18:26,912
[SPEAKER_07]: Seconded by Member Reinfeld.

767
01:18:27,752 --> 01:18:28,432
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, roll call.

768
01:18:29,863 --> 01:18:30,463
[SPEAKER_00]: Member Grambling?

769
01:18:31,104 --> 01:18:31,344
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

770
01:18:32,564 --> 01:18:33,025
[SPEAKER_00]: Member Graham?

771
01:18:33,385 --> 01:18:33,625
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

772
01:18:34,305 --> 01:18:34,965
[SPEAKER_00]: Member Olopade?

773
01:18:35,526 --> 01:18:35,866
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes.

774
01:18:36,626 --> 01:18:37,247
[SPEAKER_00]: Member Rheinfeldt?

775
01:18:39,128 --> 01:18:39,388
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

776
01:18:40,088 --> 01:18:40,768
[SPEAKER_01]: Member Rousseau, yes.

777
01:18:41,389 --> 01:18:45,951
[SPEAKER_01]: Mayor Longo Kern is absent, and Member McLaughlin is absent.

778
01:18:46,111 --> 01:18:49,432
[SPEAKER_07]: Five in the affirmative, zero in the negative, two absent, motion passes.

779
01:18:50,613 --> 01:18:52,034
[SPEAKER_07]: Are there any other motions for tonight?

780
